article.headline: Alabama St. 80, MVSU 67
article.story: MONTGOMERY, Ala. -- Brandon Brooks and Andrew Hayles scored 16 points apiece to lead Alabama State past Mississippi Valley State 80-67 on Monday night for the Hornets' fourth straight win. Alabama State (13-8, 10-1 Southwestern Athletic Conference) has won 11 of its last 12 after starting the season 2-7. The Delta Devils (3-21, 3-8), who have lost four straight, were 22-for-69 from the field, compared to the Hornets' 29-for-52. Alabama State bolted to a 10-0 lead in the first 5:56, but Mississippi Valley State scored 13 unanswered points. The Hornets closed out the half with a 16-5 run to lead 36-26. The Delta Devils cut the deficit to 41-35 with 16:39 left, but were held scoreless for more than three minutes and the Hornets regained a double-digit lead. Eric Petty had 14 points and 11 rebounds for the Delta Devils and Tashan Newsome added 14 points.
